      <div class="msgContentFrame">Ok, yeah, so I know everyone loves Feint and all but... <br /> <br />I'm planning on building as a dual class Lancer/Marauder from the ground up and mix/matching across them both. <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706">Feint</a> is nice for misses, but is it really worth gimping your accuracy on everything else for the one attack? Last thing I want is to be a one trick pony that spams <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27724" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27724">Heavy Thrust</a> and <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706">Feint</a> all day.  <br /> <br />Granted I'm not high enough yet to get <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706">Feint</a>, but is it going to be better to run with a 50% miss rate (50% less TP generation) just to benefit from a spam-able <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27706">Feint</a>? Or will I get more out of a <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27585" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27585">Speed Surge</a> / 90% hit rate (90% TP generation) with a spam-able 500 TP power like <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26985" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26985">Skull Sunder</a>?  <br /> <br />I'm not sure how it would all work, but to me instead of gimping my accuracy across the board, it may be better to pump my evade/parry and ride that wave instead. Right now I'm really liking the lancer weapons higher Parry bonus using skills like <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26867" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26867">Foresight</a> followed by <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26981" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26981">Fracture</a>.  <br /> <br />I'm also looking to combine <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26878" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26878">Murderous Intent</a> with <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27588" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27588">Invigorate</a>. Not sure though if it will give a good Crit rate increase while maintaining the TP generation (buff canceling the debuff). Maybe someone out there has tried this and can comment? <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 23rd 2010 12:21am by Kedd </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4687552" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4687552">River Wilde</a> </div></div>
