      <div class="msgContentFrame">Given you'll probably miss 33% of the time regardless of what ever stat you decide to pump; using Feint is definitely worth every bit of that 250TP. It'll be like converting a 33% miss rate into a 300% damage boost (almost doubling your damage dealing capabilities.) Besides nothing says you're reduced to Feint, it's a suppliment, you'll be hardpressed spending all your TP on feint. It's not going to stop you from spamming SS/Trammel.  <br />You talk like Lancers have the choice of running '90% hit rate,' reality is; I have no control over my accuracy other than keeping up to date with my latest gear (and using Still Precision - although to be honest that skill isn't even worth using in the middle of a fight.) <br />Ultimately, you'll find the 25% increase in cooldowns and reduced damage from subbed weaponskills to be not really worth using at all. Out of all the skills pre 15, the only ones that I'd recommend setting on a Lancer's bar are Provoke, Taunt and Raging Strike (over Ferocity, it's just that much better than it.) Lancer skills are good enough to stand on their own, no subjobs required.</div>
