      <div class="msgContentFrame">From what I have seen as a 14 lancer with a Harpoon and 4 copper rings, you are still going to be missing plenty to be able to make use of Feint when it is off cooldown.  I am really looking forward to Feint, personally. <br /> <br />About the Murderous Intent and Invigorate combo, I did just get a chance to try out Invigorate and found it to not quite be all that useful when soloing though if you are planning to be a damage dealer in a party setting, Invigorate would let you Spam those 3000 TP Doomspikes.  I would think when soloing, Murderous Intent alone would treat you well enough and that you can find some better use for those 3 Action Points (May I suggest Second Wind or Shock Spikes). <br /> <br />Regarding Foresight and Fracture, these could be useful when soloing though they really aren't particularly synergistic with the Lancer role: they feel too tank-y to me and are probably better suited for someone more on the Marauder side than Lancer side of the fence.  Do keep in mind that if you are fighting something with TP attacks that really make you quiver in your level 1 starter boots because the game's craft system is whack and though you are a rank 9 leatherworker and can make a pair of new boots, you lack the rank 34 blacksmithing rank required to make the steal toe ingredient you need for the boot recipe, you always have Moonrise.</div>
