 and ride that wave instead. Right now I'm really liking the lancer weapons higher Parry bonus using skills like <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26867" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26867">Foresight</a> followed by <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26981" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26981">Fracture</a>.  <br /> <br />I'm also looking to combine <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26878" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=26878">Murderous Intent</a> with <a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27588" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/en/ability.html?ffxivability=27588">Invigorate</a>. Not sure though if it will give a good Crit rate increase while maintaining the TP generation (buff canceling the debuff). Maybe someone out there has tried this and can comment? <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 23rd 2010 12:21am by Kedd </span></i></div></div> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />From my experience so far using life surge really helps not just you, but the whole melee in the party become more accurate.  The odd miss you get you have feint to deal loads more damage than a regular hit, which makes Fat Dodo or any mob which lowers accuracy a dream as you want to miss.  If TP is an issue, then use invigorate and comrade in arms. <br /> <br />You will definetly want to level several jobs to make a very hybrid character.  So for solo you can have bloodbath and second wind and possibly even provoke if you are duoing with a mage, all of these will be swapped for more party oriented actions. <br /> <br />Hope this makes sense,just woke up and not had coffee yet <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 23rd 2010  4:58am by MisterGaribaldi </span></i></div>
